n","text":"A balance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is not of the language of the Arabs: (O:) [i. e., it is post-classical:] it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an assay-balance"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miyzaAnN","text_ar":"مِيزَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoyaArN","text_ar":"مَعْيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for gold;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because of the form of a bird, or because of its lightness: or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"balance for dirhems"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moneys"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is known among them"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who use it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the appellation of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qArsTwn","text_ar":"قارسطون"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"χαριστίων","text_ar":"χαριστίων","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Archimedes, (as is observed in a note in p. 178 of vol. ii. of the sec. ed. of Har,) i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hydrostatic balance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, accord. to El-Fenjedeehee, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tongue"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAt","text_ar":"لِسَات"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the balance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har pp. 549-50.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","O"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}